        "id": 284251,
        "name": "",
        "username": "PiCob",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/picob/{size}/589_2.png",
        "created_at": "2026-02-09T16:48:32.969Z",
        "cooked": "<p>That screen originates from the app and isn\u2019t a phishing attempt. Like the message below tells you, it\u2019s supposed to help you regularly checking you\u2019ve still got the correct key at hand. If you\u2019re confident, you can simply skip it (or check it manually in the backup settings). IIRC, there\u2019s also a setting to turn off this prompt (maybe it was on Android only).</p>",
