        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"nickster\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"74645\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/2acd7d/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> nickster:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Signal will never ask for verification codes</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>This is said specifically in the section about Signal support. Meaning, <em>Signal support</em> will never ask for these, not the app itself.</p>",
